node.title: COVID-positive man spent three days in Gold Coast community while infectious, Premier confirms
node.alt: A side shot of a shopping centre with a christmas tree outside.
node.description: Queensland Health yesterday afternoon issued a public health alert for contact tracing locations on the Gold Coast after confirming the new positive COVID-19 case.
node.content:
["A man who tested positive to COVID-19 on the Gold Coast yesterday is fully vaccinated and was infectious in the\u00a0community for three days,\u00a0Premier Annastacia Palaszczuk says.", "She said he was\u00a0\"unlikely\" to\u00a0have the Omicron variant but investigations\u00a0were continuing.\u00a0", "Queensland Health yesterday afternoon\u00a0issued a public health alert for contact tracing locations on the Gold Coast after\u00a0confirming the\u00a0new positive COVID-19 case.", "At the time it said investigations were underway to determine the source of infection, but confirmed the man had visited the Robina Town Centre during the Black Friday shopping sales.", "Anyone who had visited the location or has symptoms \"no matter how mild\" was urged to get tested immediately.", "Ms Palaszczuk said Queenslanders must stay vigilant while work was being done to understand the new Omicron variant.", "\"There is much we are still learning about the new variant, we know that the Delta variant spreads faster than early forms of the virus and can cause more extreme infection,\" the Premier told state parliament.", "\"That's why it is important people keep getting vaccinated, keep using the check-in app and keep getting tested if they are symptomatic.\"", "Ms Palaszczuk said there are two other cases which have been detected in hotel quarantine after interstate travel, bringing the state's active case total to 18.", "There were two mystery COVID-19 cases detected on the Gold Coast last month, but last week Acting Chief Health Officer Peter Aitken said because no\u00a0other cases had been found for 14 days that\u00a0cluster\u00a0was considered \"closed\".", "All of Robina Town Centre, from 1:30pm to 2:45pm on Friday, November 26, was deemed a low-risk contact site.", "The centre's Target, Rebel Sport and JB HiFi stores were\u00a0listed as casual contact sites between 1:30pm and 2:30pm on the same day.", "There were long lines at testing centres near the shopping centre, including Mudgeeraba, on Wednesday afternoon.", "", "
A busy COVID testing clinic in Mudgeeraba on the Gold Coast on December 1, 2021.(ABC News: Steve Keen)
", "The Old Fernvale Bakery on the Brisbane Valley Highway at Fernvale, west of Brisbane, was also listed as a casual contact site for between 3:30pm and 4:05pm on Saturday, November 27.", "Owners of the bakery said on Facebook they had been advised by Queensland Health that a double-vaccinated COVID-positive person signed in.", "They said CCTV footage was being reviewed to establish if the person actually entered the shop or had contact with any person.", "But they added that of the three staff in attendance, two were fully vaccinated adults and the other was an unvaccinated 14-year-old, that they were all well and being tested.", "Authorities encouraged people to regularly monitor the list of exposure venues on the Queensland Health website and follow the public health advice, as there may be more locations posted."]
